[PKDR] Commands:
 > pkdr import <env> (to import a specific environment)
 > pkdr import --all (to import complete)
 > pkdr export <env> (to export a specific environment)
 > pkdr export --all (to export complete)
 > pkdr add <env> <package> (to add specific package to specific environment)
 > pkdr enter <env> (to enter inside a specific environment to use installed tools)
 > pkdr install <env> (to initialize the specific environment)
 > pkdr install -a (to initialize all environments)
 > pkdr list (to view all available environments)
 > pkdr show <env> (to show installed packages of the specific environment)
 > pkdr -v | pkdr --version (to view the current pkdr version)
 > pkdr update (to update pkdr)
 > pkdr remove (to remove pkdr)

[PKDR] Details:
   PKDR is a termux utility built to presist the environment state to resume on any device, by saving it to a pkdr directory.
   Developed by Nishit Samar (AlloyDark) — 2026
    